⊗-SUPER MARIO SCRALAXY-⊗ ¶A History...¶¶Use ¬arrows and Z¬ to ¬select an option¬.
¬Super Mario Scralaxy¬ is the first game by the ¬Scralaxy Team¬, development was started by ®Pickleodeon® on ¬21st May 2017¬...

The name ¬"Scralaxy Team"¬ was used later. While ¬initially¬ there was ¬no official group name¬, with the group ¬referring to itself¬ simply as ¬"Super Mario Scralaxy"¬, ¬"SMS"¬ or ¬"Team Pickelodeon"¬.
Although ®Pickleodeon® ¬stopped development¬ on the game ¬later that year¬, the ¬rest of the team¬ continued to ¬develop the game¬.
The game was ¬not planned¬ to be a fan game of ¬Super Mario Galaxy¬, but more a ¬culmination¬ of ¬past 3D Mario games¬.
"Now that we have the physics engine all worked out  we should start level design. This will be an exploration based game like Mario 64..." - ¬An old studio comment from ¬®Pickleodeon®
In the ¬early development¬ of the game, ¬updates¬ were ¬released quickly¬ and there were ¬many experimental features¬ at the time.
Many ¬sprites and assets¬ were ¬drawn at this point¬, with many being from ®Misterythefox13®, who developed the ¬original art-style characters in the game¬ possess.
¬Most sprites¬ were initially in a ¬bitmap¬ format, with them all eventually being ¬redrawn as vector sprites¬ later on.
A ¬scrolling version¬ of the game was tested early, but it was ¬decided it was too laggy/buggy¬ at that point. A ¬scrolling engine¬ would be ¬implemented 5 years¬ later by ¬ToadFanSchool¬.
¬Around v0.3.0s release¬, ®Pickleodeon® ¬announced¬ that he was "stepping down as the lead dev of [the] project." and that ¬everything else¬ would be up to ¬the decision¬ of the ¬remaining members¬.

A bit after this, a ¬"dibs"¬ project was made by ®DoritoDude123® to ¬organise who was making planned updates¬. Here ¬project members¬ could ¬claim updates¬, signifying they would be ¬developing that update¬.
On the ¬5th August 2018¬, the ®ScralaxyTeam® account was ¬created¬, giving a space to ¬organise various resources¬, such as the ¬idea vault¬.
Around the ¬24th August 2018¬, the ¬Scralaxy Team 'Fandom' Wiki¬ was created, ¬documenting¬ the entire ¬Scralaxy Team¬ and ¬their games¬.
¬Version 0.5.0¬ was released on ¬15th September 2018¬, marking the halfway point of the development of ¬Super Mario Scralaxy¬!

¬Around 2021¬ the ¬updates seemed to stagnate¬. The cause of this is not clear, but can be attributed to ¬members moving on from Scratch¬,¬life getting busier¬ or ¬updates taking longer¬... ¬Super Mario Scralaxy¬ was in ¬limbo¬.
¬Luckily¬ around the ¬end of 2021¬, several ¬team members¬ returned to the project to ¬continue developing updates¬...
...and at this ¬present day¬ updates continue...

Mario¶¬Mario is the main character of the game. His jumps aren't high, but they aren't low either. Same for his speed. He's good with beginners.¬
Luigi¶¬Luigi is Mario's twin brother. He can jump quite a bit higher than Mario. After overcoming his fear, he is ready for a new adventure!¬
Stefano¶¬Stefano is Mario and Luigi's long lost third brother. He was lost in a far away galaxy for years, but was rescued by a woman in a blue dress and is now ready for a new adventure!¬
Wario¶¬Wario's not the fastest, but he is pretty powerful! His weight might even help him get to secret areas... and nab that gold!¬
Waluigi¶¬Waluigi time! Waluigi is super fast and a good swimmer. He's also just awesome, I mean... who doesn't like a strange skinny man with a pointy moustache yelling 'WAH' all the time?¬
Wafano¶¬His family relationship with Wario and Waluigi is unknown... He can jump high, run at an average speed and is able to perform a powerful kick attack!¬
Captain Toad¶¬The leader of the Toad Brigade is joining the adventure! Usually he's unable to jump, but with his new hover springboard, he can get around with ease!¬
Shell Pong¶¬A flying shell bounces around the stage. You need it to bounce it using your paddle as many times as you can! Use the arrow keys to move Mario.¬
Toad Pong¶¬The classic table tennis game pong, but with Toads! Blue Toad uses the arrow keys and Yellow Toad uses WASD. The Toads cannot jump, so work together!¬
Stefano Fly¶¬Stefano has grabbed a Red Star, so he can fly! Use the up and down arrow keys to move and collect coins to increase your score. If you miss one, it will reset.¬
Find Luigi¶¬Luigi is hiding on the screen somewhere... click or tap his quickly to score the most points, but be careful to not click on anything else!¬
Paratroopa Hunt¶¬Click the flying Paratroopas to zap them. If you zap something else, or let the Paratroopas fly away, it's game over!¬

bpS.text:
NEW LEVELS:

How to use:
The level progression HAS to follow the list below. Every room in the castle is designed for these levels, so don't add your own.
There already are some level graphics you could use. Check them out in the "Graphics for New Levels" project over at https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/369992445
Music should be chosen when the scralaxy is made unless otherwise specified.
Minibosses and bosses can be found by searching for them on Google, they are all Mario characters.
Please try to follow the level design, ask me (@redyoshi857) if you have any questions.

Tiki Tropic Scralaxy
Miniboss: Donkey Kong
Level Design: A tiki village on a beach, then a treehouse with a Donkey Kong-style level similar to the New Donk City Festival.

Spooky Space Scralaxy
Music: Yoshi's Island castle theme??
Level Design: A ghost house, both from the outside and inside 

Shipwreck Scralaxy
Music: Dire Dire Docks
Boss: Triclyde
Level Design: A shipwreck boss scralaxy.

Searing Sand Scralaxy
Music: NSMBU Desert Theme
Miniboss: Fryguy
Level Design: The original World 2 from 0.4.7.

Tree Maze Scralaxy
Music: Beware the Forest's Mushrooms from Super Mario RPG
Level Design: A level progression maze with a dense forest theme (like if SMW Forest of Illusion was a level)

Sweet Sweet Scralaxy
Music: Sweet Sweet Kingdom (MK8D)
Miniboss: Birdo
Level Design: A mix of Sweet Sweet Kingdom and Sweet Sweet Galaxy. Maybe a little Luncheon Kingdom mixed in?

Flashback Scralaxy
Level Design: 2-3 from SM3DL

Fire Castle Scralaxy
Music: Some Mario castle music, choice of whoever makes the scralaxy.
Boss: Bowser
Level Design: A fiery castle. 'Nuff said.

Shiver Cliff Scralaxy
Miniboss: Chief Chilly
Level Design: An ordinary snow level.

Giant Block Scralaxy
Miniboss: Goomboss
Level Design: World 4 from SMB3

Mesa Mine Scralaxy
Level Design: A gold mine underneath a mesa. Featuring a more advanced version of the Deep Delve Scralaxy minecart track

Ice Slide Scralaxy
Music: Slider from SM64
Level Design: An icy level based on sliding and racing a penguin.

Shiverburn Scralaxy
Boss: Two bosses, one for fire and one for ice
Level Design: A level with both fire and ice.

Raging Flame Scralaxy
Miniboss: Wart
Level Design: Ordinary lava level.

Metropolis Scralaxy
Music: something from Mario Kart
Level Design: A large city with big architecture and moving lights

Fire Factory Scralaxy
Miniboss: Tatanga
Level Design: A factory. Also kind of orange and filled with fire.

Moon Base Scralaxy
Music: Moon Kingdom
Level Design: A moon base, of course.

Summit Scralaxy
Music: Silence before the boss rush, then boss music, then silence after that.
Bosses: Dry Bowser, King Boo, Boolossus
Level Design: A boss rush on the volcano summit which reaches up to space. Starts with Dry Bowser who is angry at Mario for killing him, then King Boo appears and reveals he was the pilot of the UFO and the unknown force Wart and Tatanga were working with. Once he is defeated, he uses the last Grand Star to transform into Boolossus. After he is defeated, the power star is collected and the ending happens.

brF.text:
HOW TO CREATE SCROLLING STAGES:

Creating scrolling stages is the exact same as creating a standard, non-scrolling stage, except there are a few extra things you need to do:

============[ SPECIFY STAGE CHUNKS ]============

Go to the "[LevelData] Stage chunks" list and go to the item with the index of your stages' star/mission (known as Stage ID or "stage" variable). Once you've found the matching stage ID index, put all the costume numbers (aka level IDs) of your stage inside the list item seperated with commas (with no spaces). Reload the stage and it should now support scrolling!

If you're confused by the seperate stage and level IDs, think of them as this:

STAGES - the ID of the whole stage/mission/star

LEVELS - the ID of an individual chunk/costume of a stage

Note: If you include a boss at the end of your stage, it is recommended that you do not include the boss costume/level ID or anything beyond it in the list item. This will allow for the boss part of your stage to be on a static screen. Remember to disable backtracking by going to the item with the boss costume/level ID index in the "[LevelData] ScreenParameters" list and making the first digit zero!

============[ MAKING A PARALLAX BACKGROUND ]============

By making your stage scroll-compatible, you may have noticed that the background has reverted to the default green hills. This is because the backdrops your stage uses don't have an associated parallax background(s). Head to the Parallax Background sprite and follow the instructions there to create a new parallax background. (In short, you need to create a parallax background version of the stage's backdrop(s) and assign them to the backdrop IDs)

============[ MAX SCROLL Y HEIGHT ]============

By default, your stage won't include any vertical scrolling. If you want the camera to be able to scroll higher up, then you can increase the max scrollY height by modifying the item with the index of your stage ID (not level ID) in the "[LevelData] Max scrollY height" list.

============[ GROUND DECORATION ]============

If you want to create any ground decoration that scrolls with the rest of the stage but isn't solid or interactable, go to the Ground Decoration sprite and read the note there.

bs@.text:
HOW TO USE CUSTOM BLOCK
PLEASE BACKUP THE LISTS BEFORE MAKING ANY IMPORTANT CHANGES INCASE YOU MAKE A MISTAKE!!

type / instant -> text you want to write ( typewrites it or displays it instantly )

Size -> Size of text

Pos -> Starting x and y positions of text

Anim -> What animation (if any) the text should use, set to 0/blank to not animate. There are two animations currently.

Wrap at -> Where the text should wrap as an x value (240 is often used), leave blank to not wrap

Group -> What group the text is part of, you can set this to anything or leave blank to set it to a 'BLANK' group

Col/bright -> The colour and brightness of the text, set brightness to 100 for white text, overwritten if text has a "highlight" attribute ( SEE LATER )

Tags -> Special effects the text could use, current you can choose from r > rainbow , s > shaking or w > waving.

delay / speaking delay -> How long it takes for each letter to show , if the typewriting will adhere to grammar rules and slow down the text with punctuation ( SEE LATER ).

Volume -> The volume the sounds the appearing text makes

bs[.text:
The list "[TextRender] widths" will show you all the supported characters. (The list is a global variable to save RAM usage)

"[TextRender] textBackgroundData" and "[TextRender] textHighlightData" store information for background positions, animations and text colours and brightnesses when certain characters are used, for instance:

"[TextRender] textPause" contains symbols that will pause the text writing briefly, basically punctuation- it makes for a more natural reading experience.

---HIGHLIGHTS---

¬ > BLUE HIGHLIGHT text

¡ > DARK BLUE HIGHLIGHT text

® > GOLD HIGHLIGHT text

⊗ > PURPLE HIGHLIGHT text

These highlight symbols work as a toggle, an example usage being:
Hello! My name is ¬Toad¬! I have ®coins®!
This would highlight 'Toad' in blue and 'coins' in gold.

"[TextRender] textHighlightData" and the 'highlightCheck' custom block stores this colour information.


---LINE BREAK---

Use '¶' in a string to break a line instantly


---SYMBOLS---

火 > Fire flower

✰ > Power star

氷 > Ice flower

粘 > Goo flower

姫 > Princess Peach

金 > Coin

時 > Time

Feel free to add more symbols as necessary, here kanji (Chinese characters) are being used to represent them to make it easier, and avoid the chance of reusing another symbol.

If you have any questions, please message @hasanmajid10 or @kino016874 's profile.

btf.text:
COSTUME NAME FORMAT:

1-1-1
[bg style]-[bg variant]-[bg layer]

=====================================

bg-style - the background theme id, e.g. grass land, forest, sky, etc

bg variant - the subtle variants of each bg for different screens (e.g. hills in different positions) NOTE: 3 variants is the default, but it can also be more or less. The amount of variants for each bg style is determined by the "Parallax BG variants/layers" list (read bottom of note).

bg layer - 3 = furthest away (e.g. clouds, far away hills), 2 = middle (usually the most defining part of the background e.g. tallest hills, pyramids, structures), 1 = closest to player/ground (e.g. low down hills, bushes, bg water) NOTE: 3 layers is only the default, it can also be more or less. The amount of layers for each bg style is determined by the "Parallax BG variants/layers" list (read bottom of note).

There is also a sprite for the non-scrolling part of the bg (usually just a gradient or stars), which is [bg style]-X-X. This is just this sprite but not a clone. The reason this exists is so existing backdrop costumes don't need to be edited, as some stages have a non-scrolling section at the end (e.g. boss) where the parallax scripts/clones are not active, the backdrop costumes might be visible there. THIS DOES NOT COUNT AS A PARALLAX LAYER.

=====================================

IMPORTANT INFO:

-The bg-style loaded is chosen through the "Backdrop -> Parallax BG ID" list. As the name implies, the position of each item is associated with a backdrop costume, and the value of each item is the parallax bg ID (or bg-style) applied when the associated backdrop costume is active. For example, the item of index 8's value is one. This means when a stage is loaded with backdrop no. 8, bg-style 1 is applied.

-Even if it wouldn't be visible, create a new backdrop costume if you want to create a new parallax background that isn't based of an existing backdrop. It doesn't need to have any detail though, unless you plan on making a non-scrolling section at the end, e.g. boss, by removing the last couple of level chunks from the "stage chunks" list. The reason the parallax bg id / bg-style relies on existing backdrop costumes is for compatibility. It can't be based on the stage ID since stages can change backdrops mid-stage (e.g. underground pipe section), unless we change they way those are handled, so it is based on the "Backdrops" list/costumes.

-You don't need to make parallax backgrounds for non-scrolling stages, such as Peach's Castle or Windows XP Scralaxy, only if you're building a stage that features scrolling.

-If you make changes to the "Parallax BG variants/layers" list, the clones will only know the new amount of layers/variants once the clones are refreshed. IT MUST BE FORMATTED X/X (variants/layers) (one digit each, left being no. of variants, right being no. of layers)

btj.text:
Ground decoration are non-interactable sprites that scroll with and are placed behind the ground chunks/objects. They can also be used in non-scrolling stages. Uses for ground decoration could include bushes, arrow signs, small buildings, building interiors, etc.

HOW TO MAKE NEW GROUND DECORATION:

Find the ID of the level chunk you want to make ground decoration for. Then, open to the "Level ID -> Ground Deco ID list" and go to the index of that level chunk costume ID / level ID (same thing). Then, set the value of the item at that index to the costume number of the ground deco you want.
